how do i know if i need to use whole disk encryption stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how do i know if i need to use whole disk encryption categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how do i know if i need to use whole disk encryption search this site the best solution for protecting the university's data is remove all restricted and confidential data from your computer if you can otherwise there is no single solution to protect the university's data any faculty or staff member using a desktop or laptop that is storing stanford restricted and or confidential data is strongly encouraged to use whole disk encryption whole disk encryption increases the protection of this data in the event the desktop or laptop is missing or stolen there is a audit report available to confirm this system was encrypted at the time it went missing mitigating the need to publicly report the stanford data as missing not sure if your workstation data is restricted or confidential check the information security office data classification guidelines for more information about whole disk encryption see the stanford whole disk encryption swde web page workstation encryption workstation encryption stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
